Chicken Fettucine Alfredo

2 tbsp olive oil
12 oz (1 large) boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cut crosswise into 1/2" strips
kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste
2 c heavy cream
1 tsp lemon zest
2 garlic cloves, grated
pinch red pepper flakes + more for garnish
1 lb dried fettucine
1 1/2 c freshly grated parmesan cheese
3 tbsp butter
chopped fresh parsley for garnish

In a 1" skillet, heat the olive oil over medium high heat. Season the chicken with salt and pepper, then cook, stirring as needed until golden brown, 4 min. Add the heavy cream, lemon zest, garlic, and pepper flakes, and bring to a simmer. Cook until reduced by half, 7 min. Meanwhile, in a large pot of boiling salted water, cook the fettucine until al dente, 10-12 min. Drain, reserving 1/4 c of the pasta water, and add to the pan, along with the grated paremsan and butter. toss the pasta until well coated, then season with salt and pepper. Transfer to a platter and garnish with pepper flakes and chopped parsley.
